<p data-start="62" data-end="388"><strong data-start="62" data-end="388">“As you know, the most important part of a resume is projects. Since I am not from a B.Tech background, I need to demonstrate that I am capable of doing practical work. So, what is the best way to present my projects? Should I include one Excel project, one SQL project, one Power BI project, or create combined projects?”</strong></p>
<hr data-start="390" data-end="393">
<p data-start="395" data-end="470">Now here’s the <strong data-start="410" data-end="466">best strategy (no confusion, just the smartest path)</strong> 🧠✨</p>
<h2 data-section-id="aqrj94" data-start="472" data-end="507">🔥 What you SHOULD do (Best Way)</h2>
<p data-start="509" data-end="579">👉 <strong data-start="512" data-end="552">Go with 2–3 STRONG COMBINED PROJECTS</strong><br data-start="552" data-end="555">
Not separate small ones.</p>
<p data-start="581" data-end="684">Why?<br data-start="585" data-end="588">
Because companies don’t want “tool users”<br data-start="629" data-end="632">
They want <strong data-start="642" data-end="684">problem solvers who use tools together</strong></p>
<hr data-start="686" data-end="689">
<h2 data-section-id="1aznde2" data-start="691" data-end="727">🎯 Ideal Resume Project Structure</h2>
<h3 data-section-id="o5rgjf" data-start="729" data-end="782">✅ Project 1 (End-to-End Project) ⭐ MOST IMPORTANT</h3>
<p data-start="783" data-end="822">Use <strong data-start="787" data-end="822">Excel + SQL + Power BI together</strong></p>
<p data-start="824" data-end="876">Example:<br>
👉 <strong data-start="836" data-end="876">Sales Performance Analysis Dashboard</strong></p>
<p data-start="878" data-end="893">What you’ll do:</p>
<ul data-start="894" data-end="999">
<li data-section-id="mcf8i2" data-start="894" data-end="924">
<p data-start="896" data-end="924">SQL → extract &amp; clean data</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="sotxkv" data-start="925" data-end="963">
<p data-start="927" data-end="963">Excel → additional cleaning / KPIs</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="sa9el5" data-start="964" data-end="999">
<p data-start="966" data-end="999">Power BI → dashboard &amp; insights</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1001" data-end="1101">This shows:<br>
💥 Real analyst workflow<br data-start="1037" data-end="1040">
💥 Strong practical skills<br data-start="1066" data-end="1069">
💥 Higher chances of selection</p>
<hr data-start="1103" data-end="1106">
<h3 data-section-id="qdfm1p" data-start="1108" data-end="1141">✅ Project 2 (Focused Project)</h3>
<p data-start="1142" data-end="1156">Pick 1–2 tools</p>
<p data-start="1158" data-end="1174">Example options:</p>
<ul data-start="1175" data-end="1256">
<li data-section-id="t5f4w0" data-start="1175" data-end="1215">
<p data-start="1177" data-end="1215">Excel Dashboard (HR / Finance / Sales)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="tlqh87" data-start="1216" data-end="1256">
<p data-start="1218" data-end="1256">SQL Data Analysis (queries + insights)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1258" data-end="1261">
<h3 data-section-id="1gptm15" data-start="1263" data-end="1302">✅ Project 3 (Optional but Powerful)</h3>
<p data-start="1303" data-end="1330">Power BI advanced dashboard</p>
<hr data-start="1332" data-end="1335">
<h2 data-section-id="1tp54xy" data-start="1337" data-end="1356">❌ What NOT to do</h2>
<p data-start="1358" data-end="1462">🚫 1 Excel project + 1 SQL project + 1 Power BI project (separately basic)<br data-start="1432" data-end="1435">
→ Looks like beginner level</p>
<p data-start="1464" data-end="1499">🚫 No project<br data-start="1477" data-end="1480">
→ Instant rejection</p>
<hr data-start="1501" data-end="1504">
<h2 data-section-id="1ndxti6" data-start="1506" data-end="1523">🧠 Golden Rule</h2>
<p data-start="1525" data-end="1550">👉 <strong data-start="1528" data-end="1550">Quality &gt; Quantity</strong></p>
<p data-start="1552" data-end="1557">Even:</p>
<ul data-start="1558" data-end="1603">
<li data-section-id="1kuky2z" data-start="1558" data-end="1603">
<p data-start="1560" data-end="1603">2 strong projects = better than 5 weak ones</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1605" data-end="1608">
<h2 data-section-id="61ftxl" data-start="1610" data-end="1642">💡 Your Situation (Important)</h2>
<p data-start="1644" data-end="1653">You said:</p>
<ul data-start="1654" data-end="1719">
<li data-section-id="m39jus" data-start="1654" data-end="1672">
<p data-start="1656" data-end="1672">Excel = good ✅</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1r5jc7g" data-start="1673" data-end="1695">
<p data-start="1675" data-end="1695">SQL = forgotten ⚠️</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ool1sk" data-start="1696" data-end="1719">
<p data-start="1698" data-end="1719">Power BI = basic ⚠️</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1721" data-end="1747">👉 So your plan should be:</p>
<h3 data-section-id="10vvfzb" data-start="1749" data-end="1787">Step 1: Revise SQL (2–3 days only)</h3>
<p data-start="1788" data-end="1797">Focus on:</p>
<ul data-start="1798" data-end="1858">
<li data-section-id="1evk5vt" data-start="1798" data-end="1825">
<p data-start="1800" data-end="1825">SELECT, WHERE, GROUP BY</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1rbqt56" data-start="1826" data-end="1834">
<p data-start="1828" data-end="1834">JOIN</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1qskoew" data-start="1835" data-end="1858">
<p data-start="1837" data-end="1858">Aggregate functions</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="mhr2v6" data-start="1860" data-end="1905">Step 2: Build 1 strong project (5–7 days)</h3>
<hr data-start="1907" data-end="1910">
<h2 data-section-id="xga40q" data-start="1912" data-end="1947">🚀 Best Project Ideas (Choose 1)</h2>
<ol data-start="1949" data-end="2069">
