<hr data-start="512" data-end="515">
<h2 data-section-id="1kd39oj" data-start="517" data-end="547">🧠 Step 1: Identify Columns</h2>
<p data-start="549" data-end="575">These are <strong data-start="559" data-end="571">NOT KPIs</strong> ❌</p>
<ul data-start="576" data-end="661">
<li data-section-id="1y1ld62" data-start="576" data-end="588">
<p data-start="578" data-end="588">Employee</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="2klrod" data-start="589" data-end="607">
<p data-start="591" data-end="607">Month 1 Salary</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="b18zy6" data-start="608" data-end="626">
<p data-start="610" data-end="626">Month 2 Salary</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1mkby15" data-start="627" data-end="661">
<p data-start="629" data-end="661">Total Salary (calculated column)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="663" data-end="704">👉 These are just data (raw + calculated)</p>
<hr data-start="706" data-end="709">
<h2 data-section-id="zrusfw" data-start="711" data-end="745">🎯 Step 2: Now KPIs (Important)</h2>
<p data-start="747" data-end="778">From this table, KPIs would be:</p>
<h3 data-section-id="jf1ydm" data-start="780" data-end="792">📊 KPIs:</h3>
<ul data-start="794" data-end="940">
<li data-section-id="1qrwn5x" data-start="794" data-end="842">
<p data-start="796" data-end="842"><strong data-start="796" data-end="828">Total Salary (All Employees)</strong> = ₹1,87,000</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="15652av" data-start="843" data-end="875">
<p data-start="845" data-end="875"><strong data-start="845" data-end="863">Average Salary</strong> = ₹46,750</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1l8gxgl" data-start="876" data-end="908">
<p data-start="878" data-end="908"><strong data-start="878" data-end="896">Highest Salary</strong> = ₹58,000</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="4znbq1" data-start="909" data-end="940">
<p data-start="911" data-end="940"><strong data-start="911" data-end="928">Lowest Salary</strong> = ₹38,000</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="942" data-end="945">
<h2 data-section-id="kvim58" data-start="947" data-end="972">🔥 Why these are KPIs?</h2>
<p data-start="974" data-end="987">Because they:</p>
<ul data-start="988" data-end="1073">
<li data-section-id="fizz5n" data-start="988" data-end="1016">
<p data-start="990" data-end="1016">Summarize the whole data</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1mj04i1" data-start="1017" data-end="1044">
<p data-start="1019" data-end="1044">Help in decision making</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="39z52b" data-start="1045" data-end="1073">
<p data-start="1047" data-end="1073">Show performance quickly</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1075" data-end="1078">
<h2 data-section-id="v1ctey" data-start="1080" data-end="1106">🎮 Easy Way to Remember</h2>
<p data-start="1108" data-end="1171">👉 Table = story<br data-start="1124" data-end="1127">
👉 KPI = <strong data-start="1136" data-end="1171">summary of the story in numbers</strong></p>
<hr data-start="1173" data-end="1176">
<h2 data-section-id="1mb0q8c" data-start="1178" data-end="1202">⚡ Final Understanding</h2>
<p data-start="1204" data-end="1293">👉 KPIs are <strong data-start="1216" data-end="1249">NOT inside the table normally</strong><br data-start="1249" data-end="1252">
👉 KPIs are <strong data-start="1264" data-end="1293">calculated FROM the table</strong></p>
<hr data-start="1295" data-end="1298">
<p data-start="1300" data-end="1442" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">If you want next:<br>
I can show you 👇<br data-start="1335" data-end="1338">
✅ How to create these KPIs in Excel (formula + pivot)<br data-start="1391" data-end="1394">
