ead-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)" style="scroll-margin-top: -348px;"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="user" data-message-id="83c0a4a7-4c9a-4463-b9fa-e072b56042d5" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden items-end rtl:items-start"><div class="user-message-bubble-color corner-superellipse/0.98 relative rounded-[22px] px-4 py-2.5 leading-6 max-w-(--user-chat-width,70%)"><div class="whitespace-pre-wrap">I am working on a project where first I open my Excel workbook and a new blank sheet. Then I open the data tab and click on get data from CSV file. Then I import the data from CSV file and click on transform the button. Then a Power Query opens. Then I perform some cleaning steps on this data. And then I clicked on the home tab of Power Query and then in the new source data, then I did other source data, then I did a blank query, then a blank query opened in the Power Query. A blank sheet opened in the Power Query. Then I made a calendar. Okay, then I close and load to the calendar in data and then I check the box data modeling. And when I click it through, it says the normal window open and it says calendar table rows loaded. Okay, but when I see hospital emergency room data that was my original data, that's it says only connection only. That is why when I open Power Pivot and clicked on manage, so it just said, so it just said, it just showed only one row, calendar row, and it does not show a hospital emergency room data. So tell me how can I show emergency room data as well in the Power Pivot.</div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div aria-label="Your message actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto touch:opacity-100 duration-300 group-hover/turn-messages:delay-300 pointer-events-none opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button></div></div></div></div><span class="sr-only"><br></span></section><section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="request-WEB:7db6c802-7c43-47fb-9316-1a3dfc040aaa-61" data-testid="conversation-turn-78" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant" style=""><h4 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="d5f77bd5-b938-4726-98c2-0818b477ebe5" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="30">First, your corrected version:</p>
<p data-start="32" data-end="446"><strong data-start="32" data-end="446">“I am working on a project where I imported a CSV file into Power Query and cleaned it. Then I created a calendar table using a blank query and loaded it to the data model. However, my original hospital emergency room data is showing as ‘connection only,’ so when I open Power Pivot, I only see the calendar table and not the hospital data. How can I also show the hospital emergency room data in Power Pivot?”</strong></p>
<hr data-start="448" data-end="451">
<h2 data-section-id="17lgeb7" data-start="453" data-end="505">🎯 What’s actually happening (simple explanation)</h2>
<p data-start="507" data-end="517">Right now:</p>
<ul data-start="519" data-end="641">
<li data-section-id="kl2u1b" data-start="519" data-end="569">
<p data-start="521" data-end="569">🟢 Calendar table → <strong data-start="541" data-end="565">Loaded to Data Model</strong> ✅</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1iwzo9a" data-start="570" data-end="641">
<p data-start="572" data-end="641">🔴 Hospital data → <strong data-start="591" data-end="637">Connection Only (NOT loaded to Data Model)</strong> ❌</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="643" data-end="688">👉 That’s why Power Pivot only shows calendar</p>
<hr data-start="690" data-end="693">
<h2 data-section-id="tzbtly" data-start="695" data-end="716">🧠 Think like this</h2>
<p data-start="718" data-end="753">Power Pivot = a <strong data-start="734" data-end="753">special room 🏠</strong></p>
<p data-start="755" data-end="821">👉 Only tables that are “invited” (loaded to Data Model) can enter</p>
<p data-start="823" data-end="833">Right now:</p>
<ul data-start="834" data-end="898">
<li data-section-id="x7r1db" data-start="834" data-end="858">
<p data-start="836" data-end="858">Calendar = invited ✅</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1v52hr2" data-start="859" data-end="898">
<p data-start="861" data-end="898">Hospital data = standing outside 🚫</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="900" data-end="903">
<h1 data-section-id="154v406" data-start="905" data-end="930">✅ FIX (Do this exactly)</h1>
<h2 data-section-id="1rt21vo" data-start="932" data-end="962">🥇 Step 1: Open Power Query</h2>
<ul data-start="964" data-end="1052">
<li data-section-id="1sdfeeu" data-start="964" data-end="1006">
<p data-start="966" data-end="1006">Go to <strong data-start="972" data-end="1004">Data → Queries &amp; Connections</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="5eases" data-start="1007" data-end="1052">
<p data-start="1009" data-end="1052">Find your <strong data-start="1019" data-end="1052">Hospital Emergency Room query</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1054" data-end="1057">
<h2 data-section-id="1w0wr6e" data-start="1059" data-end="1090">🥈 Step 2: Right-click on it</h2>
<p data-start="1092" data-end="1114">👉 Click:<br>
<strong data-start="1102" data-end="1114">Load To…</strong></p>
<hr data-start="1116" data-end="1119">
<h2 data-section-id="7cg3f3" data-start="1121" data-end="1157">🥉 Step 3: Select correct options</h2>
<p data-start="1159" data-end="1175">A box will open:</p>
<p data-start="1177" data-end="1264">✔ Choose: <strong data-start="1187" data-end="1213">Only Create Connection</strong><br data-start="1213" data-end="1216">
✔ ALSO tick: <strong data-start="1229" data-end="1264">Add this data to the Data Model</strong></p>
<p data-start="1266" data-end="1290">👉 This step is CRITICAL</p>
<hr data-start="1292" data-end="1295">
<h2 data-section-id="q3gofi" data-start="1297" data-end="1319">🏁 Step 4: Click OK</h2>
<hr data-start="1321" data-end="1324">
<h2 data-section-id="bp9jxi" data-start="1326" data-end="1357">🎯 Step 5: Check Power Pivot</h2>
<ul data-start="1359" data-end="1391">
<li data-section-id="bbdov7" data-start="1359" data-end="1391">
<p data-start="1361" data-end="1391">Go to <strong data-start="1367" data-end="1391">Power Pivot → Manage</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1393" data-end="1413">👉 Now you will see:</p>
<ul data-start="1414" data-end="1454">
<li data-section-id="1o2gx" data-start="1414" data-end="1434">
<p data-start="1416" data-end="1434">Calendar table ✅</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="15hzfft" data-start="1435" data-end="1454">
<p data-start="1437" data-end="1454">Hospital data ✅</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1456" data-end="1459">
<h1 data-section-id="jpq9wd" data-start="1461" data-end="1483">🔥 Why this happened</h1>
<p data-start="1485" data-end="1556">When you first loaded data:<br>
👉 You didn’t tick:<br>
<strong data-start="1533" data-end="1556">“Add to Data Model”</strong></p>
<p data-start="1558" data-end="1572">So Excel said:</p>
<blockquote data-start="1573" data-end="1614">
<p data-start="1575" data-end="1614">“Okay, I’ll keep it as connection only”</p>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="1616" data-end="1619">
<h1 data-section-id="1p38ddb" data-start="1621" data-end="1644">⚡ Final Understanding</h1>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer"><div tabindex="-1" class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex flex-col-reverse w-fit"><table data-start="1646" data-end="1765" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="1646" data-end="1666"><tr data-start="1646" data-end="1666"><th data-start="1646" data-end="1655" data-col-size="sm" class="">Status</th><th data-start="1655" data-end="1666" data-col-size="sm" class="">Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="1685" data-end="1765"><tr data-start="1685" data-end="1725"><td data-start="1685" data-end="1703" data-col-size="sm">Connection Only</td><td data-start="1703" data-end="1725" data-col-size="sm">Not in Power Pivot</td></tr><tr data-start="1726" data-end="1765"><td data-start="1726" data-end="1739" data-col-size="sm">Data Model</td><td data-col-size="sm" data-start="1739" data-end="1765">Visible in Power Pivot</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sticky h-0 select-none end-(--thread-content-margin) self-end"><div class="absolute end-0 flex items-end" style="height: 32.7969px;"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button aria-label="Copy table" class="hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary text-token-text-secondary my-1 rounded-sm p-1 transition-opacity group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:pointer-events-none group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:opacity-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></span></div></div></div></div>
<hr data-start="1767" data-end="1770">
<h1 data-section-id="k6usuc" data-start="1772" data-end="1801">🚀 Pro Tip (Very Important)</h1>
<p data-start="1803" data-end="1828">Whenever you want to use:</p>
<ul data-start="1829" data-end="1880">
<li data-section-id="1eyq0in" data-start="1829" data-end="1846">
<p data-start="1831" data-end="1846">Relationships</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="nsevr" data-start="1847" data-end="1864">
<p data-start="1849" data-end="1864">Data modeling</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1rtcfyb" data-start="1865" data-end="1880">
<p data-start="1867" data-end="1880">Power Pivot</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1882" data-end="1935">👉 ALWAYS tick:<br>
<strong data-start="1898" data-end="1935">“Add this data to the Data Model”</strong></p>
<hr data-start="1937" data-end="1940">
<h1 data-section-id="1vivmh1" data-start="1942" data-end="1959">🎯 Final Answer</h1>
<p data-start="1961" data-end="2087">👉 Your hospital data is not showing because it is NOT loaded to Data Model<br data-start="2036" data-end="2039">
